The paper proposes a stochastic binary spiking neural network for energy-efficient and memory-compressed neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The implementation is done using CMOS technology, which is related to electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET). The proposed network is designed for image recognition tasks, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic Spike Timing Dependent Plasticity (sSTDP) for training, which is a learning rule used in artificial neural networks (cs.AR). Finally, the paper presents results on energy efficiency and performance, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
